-- Germany’s WKN to Develop Ukraine Wind Project in Crimea
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-02-02T12:16:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/germany-s-wkn-to-develop-ukraine-wind-project-in-crimea.html
Germany ’s WKN AG signed a cooperation
agreement with Ukraine authorities to develop and implement a
wind power project in Crimea.  WKN plans to build a 400-megawatt wind plant in Crimea’s
Dzhankoy and Krasnoperekopsk districts, according to a statement
published on the website of the Crimean Council of Ministers.  The project envisages $1 billion in investments, according
to the statement. It includes engineering, construction and
operation of the wind plant, according to yesterday’s statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Moscow at 
